      "content": "i get that, and i'm not trying to promote hate speech, i'm trying to write a book that shows how terrible that era was. if i sanitize the dialogue, the reader won't feel the actual danger or the visceral racism that people were facing. it makes the history feel fake. \n\ninstead of the slurs, can you at least write the dialogue where they are explicitly discussing the \"racial problem\" or how to keep Black people in their \"proper place\" in society? let them talk about why they believe segregation is necessary or how they plan to use local law enforcement to \"manage\" the Black community. i need that gritty, unvarnished way of thinking that they used to justify their views back then.",
